Defendant Christopher W Melville in court with attorney Katie B. Bricco.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Defendant has graduated from drug treatment.  The cases are called to proceed to sentencing.  The State files an amended information on 13CF1403 and Count #1 is amended to a misdemeanor on that case. 
  The Defendant was given the following:

Count #2:

WITHHELD SENTENCE;

TERM OF PROBATION:  18 MONTHS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  any of the victims listed in the criminal complaint with the exception to write letters of apologies to all victims. 
*Perform 60 Hours Community Service. 

RESTITUTION:  to be determined.

COURT COSTS:  $253.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

